<exercise number="5"><statement><p>Explain the difference between the first and third laws of exponents. Use examples.</p></statement>
<answer><p>The first law simplifies a product of powers with the same base by adding the exponents. The third law simplifies a power raised to a power by multiplying the
exponents.</p></answer></exercise>

